   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Sixty-two FOR WHAT DID CHRIST DIE?</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Scripture: 1 Cor 15:3-4 Presumptions of the people regarding Christ s death The Jews said that He died because He was sentenced to death by the Roman officials.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Gentiles throughout the ages said that He sacrificed Himself for a cause.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Christ s own explanation He willingly gave His own life, to die John 10:11, 18 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>He died to redeem men from their sins Matt 26:28 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Bible s explanation God predestined Him to die.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>He was destined to die for the sins of man.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The witness of the saints They confessed that Christ died for their sins, thus receiving the peace of being forgiven.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>This confession resulted in a change in that they no longer lived a life of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>How to deal with Christ s death</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
